text: Joseph Myles McDonnell (died 1872) was an Irish Repeal Association politician. McDonnell was elected Repeal Association MP for at a by-election in 1846—caused by the resignation of Mark Blake—but was defeated at the general election the next year. ==References== ==External links== * Category:UK MPs 1841–1847 Category:Members of the Parliament of the United Kingdom for County Mayo constituencies (1801–1922) Category:Irish Repeal Association MPs Category:1872 deaths
